__pycache__/
*.pyc

# This repo is the usage-counts destination: skill-usage/ holds one tracked file
# per machine, as metadata about the skills it counts. It is committed to a
# PUBLIC repo by deliberate choice — see README. Sharding per machine is what
# keeps several machines from ever conflicting on the same counts file.
#
# Only the atomic-write temp files stay ignored; they exist for milliseconds
# during a write and must sit next to the target to make os.replace atomic.
.skill-usage-*.tmp
